Text:
@Dag0Red

man this is obvious that your windows driver letter is not C.  the installer is trying to locate and install into drive C:\ by default and your hard drive letter is labeled differently.

I would recommend running the setup file on a computer that has drive C, or create one yourself or put usb stick and assaign it C. than you can copy the extracted files to whatever harddrive  your game is installed.

This is the fix i used for the COA DLC go to Crusader kings directory, open the interface folder,  find the coat_of_arms.txt,  Scroll down to 		texture = {
file = "gfx\\coats_of_arms\\dynasties.tga"
size = { x = 16 y = 4 }
and change the size to 
size = { x = 51 y = 1 }
this should fix it.  


(It seems to me that paradox updated the dynasties.tga that's why it takes a re-install from GG to download the new dynasties.tga which uses the new size settings in the 1.03 patch)
